-- RBC Hires Standard Bank’s Garner as Head of Metals in New York
-- B y   C h a n y a p o r n   C h a n j a r o e n ,   M a r i a   K o l e s n i k o v a   a n d   D o u g   A l e x a n d e r
-- 2013-03-18T04:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-18/rbc-hires-standard-bank-s-garner-as-head-of-metals-in-new-york.html
RBC Capital Markets  said it hired
Bruce Garner as managing director and head of metals from
 Standard Bank  Plc where he led the bank’s commodities team.  Garner will be based in New York, where he’ll oversee the
firm’s global base and precious metals business, RBC said in an
e-mailed statement. He’ll report to Bruce Macdonald, head of
commodities and electronic trading.  Garner left Standard Bank in November, where he was head of
commodities based in Singapore. Before that, he was head of
commodities sales in Europe and the Americas for Deutsche Bank
AG, RBC said. RBC Capital is a unit of  Royal Bank of Canada , the
country’s largest lender by assets.  To contact the reporters on this story:
